                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1709.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-26T15:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1915—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am happy to inform you that Department’s policy is finally understood and
                    accepted here. A canvass of the leaders of all factions and parties reveals a
                    consensus of opinion that revolution is no longer a means of power in this
                    country because of your attitude. President Jiménes coincides with this opinion
                    and believes that a long period of unprecedented prosperity is at hand.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
